  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Generalist (Law Firm)",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Company</strong></p><p>Our client, an international law firm, is seeking HR Generalist to join their team.</p><p><br /><strong>The role</strong></p><p>HR Operations & Talent</p><ul><li>End-to-end recruitment, graduate hiring and trainee development.</li><li>Contracts, onboarding, inductions, secondments and exits.</li><li>Trusted advisor to business leaders on resourcing, talent and succession.</li></ul><p>Compensation & Benefits</p><ul><li>Salary reviews, benchmarking, payroll and benefits administration.</li><li>Insurance renewals, HR budgeting and statutory compliance.</li></ul><p>HR Operations & Compliance</p><ul><li>HRIS, employee records, leave and workforce reporting.</li><li>Work pass management, regulatory surveys and legal licensing support.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>The Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in HR, Business, or equivalent.</li><li>5+ years’ HR generalist experience with strong operational and technical expertise.</li><li>Experience in international law firms preferred.</li><li>Strong knowledge of Singapore employment law and HR best practices.</li><li>Proven ability to manage demanding stakeholders, sensitive issues, and tight timelines.</li><li>Detail-oriented, results-driven, and confident in handling confidential matters.</li><li>Collaborative team player with sound judgment and maturity in ambiguous situations.</li><li>Proficient in MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint; fluent in written and spoken English.</li><li>Workday experience an advantage.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>The Next Step</strong></p><p>Interested candidates may submit their resumes via this portal or email their CVs (in Word format) to evan.lim@chaptrconsulting.com.</p><p>EA Reg No. R1217793</p><p>EA License No. 23S1593</p>",
